content:
Certainly! Below is the HTML code for the survey form, which includes a text input for the user's name, a randomly shuffled dropdown menu for selecting a fragrance, a color palette for color selection, and a submit button. The JavaScript code included will shuffle the dropdown menu options each time the page is loaded, and ensure that both a fragrance and a color are selected before allowing submission.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Fragrance Survey</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 20px;
        }
        .hidden {
            display: none;
        }
        #submitInfo {
            margin-top: 20px;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            padding: 10px;
            display: inline-block;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Favorite Fragrance Survey</h1>
    <form id="fragranceForm">
        <label for="name">Your Name:</label>
        <input type="text" id="name" name="name" required>
        <br><br>

        <label for="fragrance">Select Your Favorite Fragrance:</label>
        <select id="fragrance" name="fragrance" required>
            <!-- Options will be added by JavaScript -->
        </select>
        <br><br>

        <label for="color">Select a Color:</label>
        <input type="color" id="color" name="color" required>
        <br><br>

        <button type="submit">Submit</button>
    </form>

    <div id="submitInfo" class="hidden">
        <h2>Your Selection:</h2>
        <p id="selectedFragrance"></p>
        <p id="selectedColor"></p>
    </div>

    <script>
        const fragrances = ["Lavender", "Jasmine", "Sandalwood", "Vanilla", "Rose", "Pine"];
        const fragranceSelect = document.getElementById('fragrance');

        // Function to shuffle an array
        function shuffle(array) {
            for (let i = array.length - 1; i > 0; i--) {
                const j = Math.floor(Math.random() * (i + 1));
                [array[i], array[j]] = [array[j], array[i]];
            }
            return array;
        }

        // Shuffle fragrances and add them to the dropdown
        const shuffledFragrances = shuffle(fragrances);
        shuffledFragrances.forEach(fragrance => {
            const option = document.createElement('option');
            option.value = fragrance;
            option.textContent = fragrance;
            fragranceSelect.appendChild(option);
        });

        // Handle form submission
        document.getElementById('fragranceForm').addEventListener('submit', function(event) {
            event.preventDefault();

            const name = document.getElementById('name').value;
            const selectedFragrance = fragranceSelect.value;
            const selectedColor = document.getElementById('color').value;

            if (name && selectedFragrance && selectedColor) {
                document.getElementById('selectedFragrance').textContent = `Fragrance: ${selectedFragrance}`;
                document.getElementById('selectedColor').textContent = `Color: ${selectedColor}`;
                document.getElementById('submitInfo').classList.remove('hidden');
            }
        });
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

This code implements the survey form with the specified features. The dropdown options are shuffled each time the page is loaded, and the form requires both a fragrance and a color to be selected before submission. The selected fragrance and color are displayed after submission.
